{"parse":{"title":"Circumstantial voice","pageid":7235611,"revid":792359640,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Grammar\" title=\"Grammar\">grammar</a>, a <b>circumstantial voice</b>, or <b>circumstantial passive voice</b>, is a <a href=\"/wiki/Grammatical_voice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Grammatical voice\">voice</a> that promotes an <a href=\"/wiki/Oblique_argument\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oblique argument\">oblique argument</a> of a <a href=\"/wiki/Verb\" title=\"Verb\">verb</a> to the role of <a href=\"/wiki/Subject_(grammar)\" title=\"Subject (grammar)\">subject</a>; the underlying subject may then be expressed as an oblique argument. A given language may have several circumstantial voices, each promoting a different oblique argument. One very common circumstantial voice is the ordinary <a href=\"/wiki/Passive_voice\" title=\"Passive voice\">passive voice</a>, which promotes a <a href=\"/wiki/Patient_(grammar)\" title=\"Patient (grammar)\">patient</a> to the subject position.\n</p><p>Circumstantials are conceptually similar to <a href=\"/wiki/Applicative_voice\" title=\"Applicative voice\">applicatives</a>, which promote obliques to <a href=\"/wiki/Direct_object\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Direct object\">direct objects</a>. However, applicatives may increase the <a href=\"/wiki/Valency_(linguistics)\" title=\"Valency (linguistics)\">valency</a> of an <a href=\"/wiki/Intransitive_verb\" title=\"Intransitive verb\">intransitive verb</a> by adding a direct object, while circumstantials cannot.\n</p><p>Circumstantials are found in the <a href=\"/wiki/Malagasy_language\" title=\"Malagasy language\">Malagasy language</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Circumstantial_voice&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Trask, R. L. (1993). <i>A Dictionary of Grammatical Terms in Linguistics</i>. Routledge. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-415-08628-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-415-08628-0\">0-415-08628-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Dictionary+of+Grammatical+Terms+in+Linguistics&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.isbn=0-415-08628-0&amp;rft.aulast=Trask&amp;rft.aufirst=R.+L.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACircumstantial+voice\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Circumstantial_voice&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://literalminded.wordpress.com/2005/09/04/dougs-circumstantial-passive/\">Doug's Circumstantial Passive</a></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Linguistics_stub.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Linguistics_stub.svg/40px-Linguistics_stub.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"17\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Linguistics_stub.svg/60px-Linguistics_stub.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Linguistics_stub.svg/80px-Linguistics_stub.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"175\" data-file-height=\"74\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"